subSubSection.paragraph:
Lower surface of head in juveniles 47–115 mm SL dark brown, “lips” and distal parts of branchiostegal rays pale. A single chin barbel in a 47 mm SL juvenile with dark brown pigmentation on both sides ( Fig. 33b ). Fish 165–183 mm SL with small, usually numerous, dark specks on gill covers and under eyes (
Fig. 33g
).
